On the other hand, we know that:
$$
\text{Annual cash flow} = \text{After tax lease payment }+\text{ Lost depreciation tax shield}
$$
Therefore:
$$
\begin{align*}
\$1,395,403.48&= \text{Lease value }\times(1-0.21) + \$252,000\\[10pt]
\text{Lease value} &= \frac{\$1,395,403.48- \$252,000}{1-0.21}\\[10pt]
&= \frac{\$1,143,403.48}{0.79}\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$1,447,346.18}
\end{align*}
$$
